data.caption: I've been experiencing presents as a discomfort or pressure in the central part of my chest, right behind the breastbone. It's not an intense pain, more like a tightness or squeezing sensation. It tends to come and go, and I've noticed it doesn't necessarily coincide with physical activity.

I've been having some visual disturbances recently. Specifically, I've noticed discomfort or a sensation of glare when exposed to certain types of light. Even in moderate lighting conditions, it feels quite intense and uncomfortable.

I've been having some issues with my stomach lately. I've been experiencing recurring discomfort in my abdominal area. It's not always severe, but it's like a cramping sensation that comes and goes. Additionally, my bowel movements have been irregular. I've been alternating between episodes of constipation and diarrhea, and it's been quite unpredictable. Sometimes I feel bloated or overly full even after small meals.
